dimensions: sheet trimmed to plate: 14.4 x 10.3 cm. (5 11/16 x 4 1/16 in.)
creditline: Museum purchase, Laura P. Hall Memorial Fund
markings: Verso, stamped: Y.W. [blackletter, encircled, L.2669]; KOENIGLICHES KUPFERSTICHKABINET * / 1891 [in oval, text encircling date and inscription of number "118", variant of L.1607/L.1610]; * B * / Veraussert / * * * / K. K. [encircled, L.2482]

texts.textentryhtml: Acquired by the Kupferstichkabinett, Berlin, 1891 (inv. no. 118, "angekauft von der Direktion der Discontogesellschaft Berlin," along with inv. nr. 1891-98...164, for 10366,30M, sales of Apr. 6, 1889 and Mar. 7, 1890); deaccessioned (as duplicate) by the former, 1899, via Amsler & Ruthardt [Auction LVIII, Mar. 6, 1899, lot 734]. Heinrich Yorck von Wartenburg [1861–1923]; then to heirs who put at auction through C.G. Boerner (in Sale 176 May 2, 1932, lot 42, unsold; re-offered in Sale 179, Nov. 8-9, 1932, lot 447, once more unsold); likely back to consigner. Parke-Bernet Galleries (February 28, 1950, cat. 1352, no. 52); purchased by Princeton University Art Museum, 1950.
texts.remarks: The Kupfterstichkabinett acquisition book of 1891 includes info about this, with year and reason for deaccession. It also notes that these were bought (angekauft von der Direktion der Discontogesellschaft Berlin) along with inv. nr. 98-1891...164-1891, for 10366,30M (remark, presumably on sales dates: "I.N. / S.C.S. 6.4.89 und 7.3.90")
